data.name: Menu_FollowASample.ToolTipText
data.value: Displays all possible Fields of a Sample Record, showing default values used by HW when the Field is not present in the Record. Follows links to various related Sections, providing the same expanded Field display for the linked Records.

data.name: Status_RowTypeVal.ToolTipText
data.value: The type of the Row containing the current Line: NA - No ODF XML Header - the opening header of an ODF ODF Start-Tag - the opening <Haupterk...> tag ODF End-Tag - the closing </Hauptwerk> tag Gen Sec Data - content inside the _General Section Sec Start-Tag - Section Start <ObjectList...> Sec End-Tag - Section End </ObjectList> Record - <o>...</o> content within a Section

data.name: Status_FileDirtyVal.ToolTipText
data.value: Indicates if the ODF has been changed, but not saved back to a file. Orange - No ODF loaded. Green - ODF is unmodified from file version. Red - ODF has been modified not not saved to a file.

data.name: Status_SecDirtyVal.ToolTipText
data.value: Indicates the validity of the Section Indices. A List Sections or ODF Font-Size change will forcibly rebuild an Invalid Index. Orange - No ODF loaded Green - ODF loaded, Section Indices Valid Red - ODF loaded, Section Indicies Invalid
